オプション1: Star Man arrived near the See Poroporo Moss Garden.
(It feels like a place people shouldn't enter...)
The white person he'd met by the coconut trees was there.
Star Man looked toward them and watched for a reaction.
The white person kept staring at him expressionlessly.
"It seems we can talk, but are you human?"
"If you don't trust me, I'll go."
"I wanted to see if you have wings."
"How can I get you to trust me?"
"If I can tell you're not trying to harm me."
The experimental subject seemed not to fully understand.
"If I come here, can I meet you again?"

(I kind of want to let the kids meet them,
 but it's a little scary.)
Star Man headed for the ruins.
The experimental subject came up onto a hill. Another white person was there.
The two stood there without moving.
